# AI Feature Patterns

## API Routes — Streaming

All AI API routes use the Vercel AI SDK with streaming:

```ts
// app/api/chat/route.ts
import { streamText } from "ai"
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai"

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { messages } = await req.json()

  const result = streamText({
    model: openai("gpt-4o-mini"),
    system: buildSystemPrompt(),  // always inject content/ context
    messages,
  })

  return result.toDataStreamResponse()
}
```

## System Prompt Construction

Build system prompts from typed `content/` data — never hardcode bio/projects inline:

```ts
import { projects } from "@/content/projects"
import { bio } from "@/content/bio"

function buildSystemPrompt() {
  return `You are an AI assistant for ${bio.name}'s portfolio...
  
Projects: ${projects.map(p => `${p.title}: ${p.description}`).join("\n")}
`
}
```

## Client-Side Chat

Use `useChat` from `ai/react` for the chat UI. Keep the hook call in a `"use client"` component:

```tsx
"use client"
import { useChat } from "ai/react"

export function ChatWidget() {
  const { messages, input, handleInputChange, handleSubmit } = useChat({
    api: "/api/chat",
  })
  // ...
}
```

## Caching AI Responses

For expensive/deterministic AI calls (project summaries), use the `"use cache"` directive from Next.js 16:

```ts
async function getProjectSummary(projectId: string) {
  "use cache"
  // result is cached — won't re-run on every request
  const result = await generateText({ ... })
  return result.text
}
```
